Samson Folarin The Commissioner of Police in Lagos State, Hakeem Odumosu, on Tuesday said the command would not compromise the enforcement of traffic rules. He stressed that the police would arrest anyone who drove against traffic, rode motorcycles on restricted routes or use the BRT lanes. A statement by the Police Relations Officer,Muyiwa Adejobi, said Odumosu spoke during a meeting with the 14 area commanders and the different heads of departments in the command at the police headquarters at Ikeja. “The police boss also ordered the area commanders to form a task force in their respective commands to enforce the order and arrest violators for immediate prosecution. “Similarly, CP Hakeem Odumosu urged Lagosians to obey traffic rules, as such would assist tremendously in the management of the traffic situation in the state. He charged all traffic management agencies to duly enforce traffic rules,” the statement added. Copyright PUNCH.
